						               													<description>Overview: Promise Reborn is a 2-4 player deck-building game where players try to deliver cards back to their Realm in order to gain Prosperity and win the game. Players begin with 6 cards in their deck, and draw 4 cards for their hand. 4 cards form a main deck is placed in the center row. On their turn, a player plays all the cards from their hand, gaining Strength and other special abilities. Players spend their Strength to either Gather cards to their discard pile, or Deliver cards to their Realm to be scored for Prosperity. At their end of their turn, the player draws 4 cards form their deck, shuffling their discard pile to form a new deck if they ever run out of cards in their deck. When a player has 20 or more Prosperity at the end of a round, the game stops. The player with the most Prosperity wins. The game is light, fast, and fun.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Story: After the Great Cataclysm the realms of Promise were shattered. Once great empires now lay in ruin. It is time to rebuild our realms, and you have been chosen to help. Explore the realmsscape in search for Artifacts, lost Knowledge, Allies, and key Resources Gather what you find to help you in your quest, or deliver them to your realm to bring prosperity. The realm with the most prosperity will be a beacon of light to all in Promise Reborn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
